{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c678cd54-51d3-4fb6-a7e8-7b643c65f7df","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob — `**\\*.*` (line 9, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is the most expensive pattern here — cost scales with the number of files on disk, and it re-runs on every evaluation.\n\n**Fix:** Scope the glob to specific extensions or directories you actually need (e.g., `**\\*.txt`), or remove it if unused.\n\n---\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function (line 13, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` during evaluation performs **synchronous disk I/O on every evaluation pass**. Property functions run in the evaluation phase (not build), so this blocks IDE responsiveness too.\n\n**Fix:** Move file reading to a build target so it only runs when actually building, not during every evaluation.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Three-level deep import chain (`imports/`)\n```\ncsproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach `<Import>` adds an extra file open + parse during evaluation. Here the chain is 3 levels deep. While manageable at this scale, deeply nested imports increase evaluation time linearly and make it harder to diagnose slow evaluations. In real projects this pattern can cascade.\n\n**Fix:** Flatten the chain — import a single `.props` file, or use `Directory.Build.props` to consolidate shared settings.\n\n---\n\n### Summary (ordered by impact)\n\n| Issue | Severity | Line |\n|---|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` recursive glob | 🔴 High | csproj:9 |\n| `File.ReadAllText` in property function | 🟠 Medium | csproj:13 |\n| 3-level nested import chain | 🟡 Low | imports/ |\n\nThe recursive glob is the primary bottleneck — it dominates evaluation time in any non-trivial directory tree.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9bce6be4-1e23-4362-85ff-afba6c5a4eac","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":585},"id":"7b20222c-9568-4808-90f3-fc14f7dd7407","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:09:20.464Z","parentId":"480013c4-ec6d-4886-892d-d5af72b99719"}
